{
  "texts": [
    "We use transformer-based methods, such as BERTopic [58], a combination of transformer-based text embedding and density-based clustering HDBSCAN [59], which can identify cohesive groups of texts in the embedding space.",
    "It is well known that BERTopic is effective for extracting more detailed topics [60] compared to other topic modeling methods such as Latent Dirichlet Allocation [61].",
    "Since BERTopic yields various numbers of clusters depending on the datasets and the parameters (we set it as default), we focus on the largest five topics.Figure 6 shows the top five topics and their sentiment by occupation.",
    "The authors assign labels to the topics through the manual examination.",
    "We select the most pronounced occupations in the difference in sentiment ratio."
  ]
}